VERSION 1
WHEN PRESENT \b(?:std::process::)?Command::new\s*\(
WHEN EXPR MISSING:validate|sanitize|allowlist|whitelist|args\s*\(\s*&\s*\[|arg\s*\(\s*"[^"]*" && MISSING:test|example
REPORT AS area_of_interest
REASON Detects command execution entry points in Rust applications.
TRACE Externalized rule logic for Shell Command Execution with std::process::Command.
